               <msContents>
                  <summary>
                    Excerpt from Computus, Computus, Baḥǝrä Ḥasab, ባሕረ፡ ሐሳብ፡;
                    Commentary on Instructions and Explanations to the Chanters in the Antiphonary for the Fast of Lent</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                    <locus from="1r" to="5v" facs="001">Fols 1r–5v</locus>
                    <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3851Hassab">We have written a
                                                  computus that we will remember in order not to
                                                  congregate with apostates...</title>
                    <incipit xml:lang="am">ባሕረ፡ አሳብ፡ ፫፻፲ወ፰ ሊቃውንት። ፩ ሊቅ፡ ድሜጥሮስ፡ ነበረ፡ <gap reason="omitted"/> ድሜጥሮስ፡ ግን፡ ከሕጉ፡ መንኖ፡ ነበረና፡ ይህ፡ የዘለዓለም፡ ቍርባን፡ ይገባል፡ በምን፡ ይቻላል፡ አሉት።
                    ፍሕም፡ ረግፆ፡ ይጸልይ፡ ነበረና፡ በጸጋ፡ አወቀና፡ <gap reason="omitted"/></incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                    <locus from="5v" to="7v" facs="006">Fols 5v–7v</locus>
                    <title>Times for the Antiphonary for the Fast of Lent, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጊዜያት፡ ዘጾመ፡ ድጓ፡</foreign></title>
                    <incipit xml:lang="gez">ጊዜያት፡ ዘጾመ፡ ድጓ፡ ፭ ናቸው፡ ምን፡ ምን፡ ቢሉ፡ ነግህ፡ ሠለስት፡ ቀትር፡ ሰዓት፡ ሠርክ፡ ከአዳም፡ እስከ፡ ኖኅ፡ ነግህ፡ ነው።
                      ከኖኅ፡ እስከ፡ አብርሃም፡ ሠለስት፡ ነው፡ ከአብርሃም፡ እስከ፡ ሙሴ፡ ቀትር፡ ነው። <gap reason="omitted"/></incipit>
                    <note>A section from the Antiphonary for the Fast of Lent containing a commentary and explanation to the chanters</note>
                </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i3"><locus from="8r" facs="008">Fols 8r and following</locus>
                  <title>The Story of Demetros and how he proved his holiness</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ‘ǝz</textLang>
                  <note>written in a different hand and in blue ink</note>
                  </msItem>
